            "releaseNotes": "<p>This release of the Splunk App for Anomaly Detection comes with several enhancements, in both the app workflow and the machine learning algorithm that powers it.</p>\n<p>The app has a new remediation workflow.  We can detect whether the input time series has missing data or is unevenly spaced.  If the data is unevenly spaced, we provide an aggregation capability to create an evenly-spaced time series.  If there is missing data, we fill it in via linear interpolation.</p>\n<p>In this version, we expand our alert actions from email only to include \u201cLog event\u201d, \u201cOutput results to lookup\u201d, \u201cOutput results to telemetry endpoint\u201d, \u201cSend to Splunk Mobile\u201d, \u201cWebhook\u201d, and \u201cAdd to Triggered Alerts\u201d.</p>\n<p>We have also enhanced our Job Dashboard.  The dropdown for each job shows its properties, including the sensitivity, the saved search schedule, and the alert actions selected for both anomaly and missing data alerting.</p>\n<p>Behind the scenes, we have also significantly improved our anomaly detection algorithm.</p>",
            "sha256": "fa6a7eb39536dfd446d47722e0d9355c6216fe878251eb5ca9851cd2326183f9",
